The paper focuses on the measurement of interpersonal trust in virtual software teams, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of virtual teams also involves issues related to communication and collaboration (cs.CY), and the paper discusses the use of software tools to support these processes (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the importance of cultural differences in global software development (cs.CE) and the use of technology to facilitate cross-cultural communication (cs.SI).
